Introduction

Special Rules Areas are defined directly beneath all Terminal Control Areas (TMAs) in South Africa, with the same lateral boundary as the TMA (potentially except for the Lowveld TMAs - just check). Special Rules Areas are designed to improve the safety for aircraft operating below the TMA and protect the TMA from potential airspace infringements through mandating procedures such as  specified altitudes and Traffic Information Broadcasts by Ai…";}s:8:"internal";a:2:{s:5:"cache";b:1;s:3:"toc";b:1;}s:8:"relation";a:1:{s:10:"firstimage";s:0:"";}}s:10:"persistent";a:5:{s:4:"date";a:2:{s:7:"created";i:1670769169;s:8:"modified";i:1671627666;}s:7:"creator";s:13:"Miguel Albano";s:4:"user";s:6:"810471";s:11:"last_change";a:8:{s:4:"date";i:1671627666;s:2:"ip";s:13:"41.150.213.92";s:4:"type";s:1:"E";s:2:"id";s:8:"faor-sra";s:4:"user";s:7:"1378824";s:3:"sum";s:22:"Added Pinedene routing";s:5:"extra";s:0:"";s:10:"sizechange";i:1391;}s:11:"contributor";a:1:{i:1378824;s:11:"Darren Hill";}}}